column2: The R.cache package needs to create a directory that will hold cache files. It is convenient to use  ‘C:\Users\èvelynee\AppData\Local\R\R.cache’ because it follows the standard on your operating system and it remains also after restarting R. Do you wish to create the 'C:\Users\èvelynee\AppData\Local\R\R.cache' directory? If not, a temporary directory (C:\Users\VELYNE~1\AppData\Local\Temp\Rtmp0AtEwL/.Rcache) that is specific to this R session will be used. [Y/n]:
